\",\n            \"seq\": 3\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"用户正在要求作为选品专家来快速筛选市场潜力产品。这是在 subagent 上下文中，我需要独立完成这个任务。\\n\\n让我思考一下这个任务：\\n1. 需要快速筛选市场潜力产品\\n2. 这是一个选品专家的任务\\n\\n我需要先了解当前的情况：\\n- 用户在飞书环境中\\n- 可能需要利用飞书相关工具\\n- 需要考虑\\\"快速筛选\\\"和\\\"市场潜力产品\\\"\\n\\n让我看看有什么可用的工具：\\n- web_search: 可以搜索市场信息\\n- web_fetch: 获取网页内容\\n- feishu_bitable_app: 多维表格，可以用来管理选品数据\\n- feishu_sheet: 电子表格，也可以用来管理数据\\n- feishu_task: 任务管理\\n\\n作为选品专家，我应该：\\n1. 先了解用户的具体需求（产品类型、市场、预算、时间等）\\n2. 搜索市场趋势和潜力产品\\n3. 分析筛选标准\\n4. 提供筛选结果\\n\\n但是用户消息是\\\"Continue where you left off\\\"，说明这是一个继续的对话，之前可能有上下文被截断了。不过既然我是subagent，而且这是第一次消息，我应该从任务描述开始工作。\\n\\n任务描述：\\\"选品专家，快速筛选市场潜力产品\\\"\\n\\n这是一个明确的任务，我应该：\\n1. 理解什么是\\\"市场潜力产品\\\"\\n2. 制定筛选标准\\n3. 选择目标市场/品类\\n4. 搜索和分析\\n5. 给出结果\\n\\n让我开始工作：\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"我是您的选品专家。让我快速帮您筛选市场潜力产品。\\n\\n首先我需要了解一些关键信息来精准定位：\\n\\n1. **目标品类**：您关注哪个行业/品类？（如：消费电子、家居用品、美妆护肤、服装配饰、食品饮料等）\\n\\n2. **目标市场**：主要销售区域？（如：中国市场、美国市场、欧洲、东南亚等）\\n\\n3. **筛选维度**：您最看重哪些方面？\\n   - 市场规模与增长趋势\\n   - 利润率\\n   - 竞争程度\\n   - 供应链可行性\\n   - 消费者需求热度\\n   - 其他（请说明）\\n\\n4. **预算与资源**：大概的采购/启动预算范围？\\n\\n请提供这些信息，我将立即开始市场调研和产品筛选，快速给您呈现潜在爆款清单。\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n          \"provider\": \"openrouter\",\n          \"model\": \"openrouter/free\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 25492,\n            \"output\": 949,\n            \"totalTokens\": 30921,\n            \"cacheRead\": 4480,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1774598843515,\n          \"responseId\": \"gen-1774598850-6EGFv5vcycc2WSnjwQbZ\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"9e74d719\",\n            \"seq\": 4\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:subagent:db04fc71-d290-400e-b807-11ab63f53934\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n      \"label\": \"tts_hair_scout_agent\",\n      \"displayName\": \"feishu:g-agent-main-subagent-db04fc71-d290-400e-b807-11ab63f53934\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:feishu:direct:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"feishu\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1774596059905,\n      \"sessionId\": \"72054f66-fa51-42ec-8ac5-c74ac0937f6f\",\n      \"model\": \"openrouter/free\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 41826,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1774593691537,\n      \"endedAt\": 1774593760988,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 66888,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/72054f66-fa51-42ec-8ac5-c74ac0937f6f.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The user is prompting \\\"你是那个agent\\\" with sender metadata \\\"openclaw-control-ui\\\". This looks like some system message - maybe the user wants to continue with tts_hair_scout skill, which is about TikTok hair accessory scouting with TTS etc. The previous attempt was to read skill definition files. The tool exec was used to find hair related files. It returned errors due to permission denied, but it also returned the path to tts_hair_scout/SKILL.md, which we have already read. So next steps: Use the tts_hair_scout skill. According to the skill description, it requires the agent-browser tool. It must be invoked with `run tts_hair_scout` from parent agent, but we are a subagent? The sub-agent context says we are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). The original instruction from user: \\\"Continue where you left off. The previous model attempt failed or timed out.\\\" So we need to continue the task which is tts_hair_scout.\\n\\nThus we need to spawn a subagent to run the tts_hair_scout skill? Or use the skill directly? The skill is defined as a subagent that runs agent-browser. The skill usage: It must be invoked by the parent agent with `run tts_hair_scout`. However, we are currently a subagent with no explicit parent. Maybe the system wants us to spawn a subagent to run the tts_hair_scout skill. The skill's own README says it's an isolated sub-agent and must be invoked by parent agent with `run tts_hair_scout`. As we are a subagent ourselves, maybe we can spawn another subagent to run the skill.\\n\\nThe tool \\\"sessions_spawn\\\" can spawn a new subagent with a given skill and parameters. The syntax: sessions_spawn(message<payload JSON>, spawnOptions). The message payload can include the required parameters for the skill. According to the skill doc, the parameters are a JSON with fields: category, subcategories, view_threshold, keywords, bitable_app_token, bitable_table_id.\\n\\nWe need to provide those parameters. The user hasn't supplied any specific values; perhaps we can use placeholder values? The skill's parameters are required. The parent agent must forward LLM scoring request and Feishu messaging/Bitable writes. But as a subagent, we need to execute the skill. Maybe we can just spawn a subagent with the required payload and then let it run. Or we can directly try to run the skill via exec? The skill is probably implemented as a subagent type that can be spawned.\\n\\nThe system may support \\\"run <skill>\\\" command? In the earlier instructions, it says: \\\"When a first-class tool exists for an action, use the tool directly instead of asking the user to run equivalent CLI or slash commands.\\\" The skill may have a command to run it: probably \\\"run tts_hair_scout\\\". But that may be a command for the parent agent, not for us.\\n\\nThe system is unclear. Let's examine the \\\"sessions_spawn\\\" tool signature:\\n\\n```\\ntype sessions_spawn = (_: {\\n// Message\\n//\\n// The message to send to the newly spawned session. Must be valid JSON.\\nmessage:     // The message to send to the newly spawned session. Must be valid JSON.\\n// JSON object\\npayload:     // The payload to send to the newly spawned session.\\nstring//\\n// Spawn Options\\n//\\n// Options for spawning a new session. Currently only `modality` and `responsibility` are supported.\\n//\\nmodality?:     // The modality of the new session. Defaults to the current session's modality, but can be overridden.\\ntype?:       // One of: text|audio|visual|tts|chat|search|recommend|triage|qa|transcribe|translate|summarize|classify|detect_entities|sentiment|intent|extract_relations|detect_translation|detect_language|detect_formatting|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_phrase_count|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detec