o provide those parameters. The user hasn't supplied any specific values; perhaps we can use placeholder values? The skill's parameters are required. The parent agent must forward LLM scoring request and Feishu messaging/Bitable writes. But as a subagent, we need to execute the skill. Maybe we can just spawn a subagent with the required payload and then let it run. Or we can directly try to run the skill via exec? The skill is probably implemented as a subagent type that can be spawned.\n\nThe system may support \"run <skill>\" command? In the earlier instructions, it says: \"When a first-class tool exists for an action, use the tool directly instead of asking the user to run equivalent CLI or slash commands.\" The skill may have a command to run it: probably \"run tts_hair_scout\". But that may be a command for the parent agent, not for us.\n\nThe system is unclear. Let's examine the \"sessions_spawn\" tool signature:\n\n```\ntype sessions_spawn = (_: {\n// Message\n//\n// The message to send to the newly spawned session. Must be valid JSON.\nmessage:     // The message to send to the newly spawned session. Must be valid JSON.\n// JSON object\npayload:     // The payload to send to the newly spawned session.\nstring//\n// Spawn Options\n//\n// Options for spawning a new session. Currently only `modality` and `responsibility` are supported.\n//\nmodality?:     // The modality of the new session. Defaults to the current session's modality, but can be overridden.\ntype?:       // One of: text|audio|visual|tts|chat|search|recommend|triage|qa|transcribe|translate|summarize|classify|detect_entities|sentiment|intent|extract_relations|detect_translation|detect_language|detect_formatting|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_phrase_count|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_keywords|detect_topics|detect_language|detect_translation|detect_entities|detect_intent|detect_sentiment|detect_relations|detect_phrase_count|detect_k