{"type":"message","id":"28507103","parentId":"55f7d1f2","timestamp":"2026-04-02T07:10:26.704Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see from the sessions list that the \"撤回选品Agent配置\" subagent did complete (status: done) - it asked for approval for git checkout. But I don't see a tts agent with id \"tts\" in the sessions list. The user is saying there's an agent with id \"tts\" name \"选品专家agent\" in the后台 (backend).\n\nLet me look for the tts agent. In the sessions list I see:\n- `tts_hair_scout_agent` with label `tts_hair_scout_agent` - this might be the one\n- There's no agent with label just \"tts\"\n  \nThe user seems to be referring to a different tts agent than the ones currently in the sessions list. I'm checking the `tts_hair_scout_agent` more carefully now - it's marked as done and has the label `tts_hair_scout_agent`, but the user is saying there's an agent with id `tts` and name `选品专家agent`. These don't seem to match up, so either the agent isn't showing in my current sessions list or it's been configured differently than what I'm seeing. I see there was a subagent called `tts_hair_scout_agent` that ran before, but it's currently in a done state. The user is pointing to a tts agent in the后台 (backend) that might be registered in the system configuration rather than just in the session history, so I need to look at the agents configuration files to find the right one they're referring to. Looking at the session history more carefully, I see there was a `tts_hair_scout_agent` that ran before, but the user is saying there's a different agent called \"选品专家agent\" with id \"tts\" that they want me to use instead of creating new subagents. They're frustrated because I've been spawning new agents when I should be using an existing one they have set up. Let me try using sessions_send to message the tts_hair_scout_agent directly and see if that works. Looking at the tts_hair_scout_agent more closely, it seems to have a defin