{"type":"message","id":"58bc41bb","parentId":"4e5dcd48","timestamp":"2026-04-02T08:26:21.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether the product-selector agent should be changed to use static registration instead of dynamic spawning. They want to know if they should convert it to a statically registered agent.\n\nAlso there's an unrelated exec denied notification about a previous grep command that timed out - I should ignore this as per instructions.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n1. The product-selector was previously created as a dynamically spawned subagent\n2. The user is asking if it should be converted to a statically registered agent (like how \"tts\" is registered)\n\nActually, looking at the agents list the user shared earlier:\n```\n- tts (TTS-选品专家)\n  Workspace: ~/.openclaw/workspace-selector\n  Agent dir: ~/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\n  Model: minimax/MiniMax-M2.7\n  Routing rules: 1\n  Routing: default (no explicit rules)\n```\n\nThe tts agent IS statically registered. The product-selector is a dynamic spawn that was used before.\n\nThe user is asking if I should register the product-selector as a static agent in agents.list. This would make sense if they want to be able to directly invoke \"选品专家\" as a known agent.\n\nBut wait - the user just corrected me on the architecture. Now they're asking if the product-selector should be statically registered so that it can be found/called properly.\n\nActually, looking at the context:\n- We just set up the \"tts\" agent properly with SOUL/TOOLS/USER\n- The tts agent is the statically registered one for 选品专家 work\n- The \"product-selector\" was just a dynamically spawned session that was used in testing\n\nSo actually the current setup is:\n- \"tts\" = statically registered 选品专家 agent (already configured)\n\n\n- \"product-selector\" = old dynamically spawned test agent\n\nThe product-selector doesn't need to be statically registered if tts is already handling the 选品专家 role. But if the user wants to be able to invoke 选品专家 directly like they do with tts, then yes - product-selector should be added to agents.list. I should confirm their intent before making changes.","thinkingSignature":"6b378c96d17b413841ce8c8b086329443f02b7ce3a5855f6681347d392fc5430"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>不一定需要。\n\n现在的架构是：\n\n- **`tts`** = 静态注册的「选品专家」，已有完整配置，可直接被 main 调用\n- **`product-selector`** = 之前测试时动态 spawn 的会话，用完就结束\n\n如果你只想保留 **一个** 选品专家，那 `tts` 静态注册就够了，product-selector 不需要注册。\n\n**但如果你想让「选品专家」有两种存在形态**（既能被 sessions_spawn 动态调用，也能像 tts 那样静态注册被 main 直接路由），那可以把 product-selector 也加到 agents.list 里做静态注册。\n\n你的意图是：\n1. **保留 tts 即可**（一个选品专家够用）？\n2. **product-selector 也要静态注册**（两种调用方式都保留）？</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39,"output":632,"cacheRead":3555,"cacheWrite":99316,"totalTokens":103542,"cost":{"input":0.0000117,"output":0.0007584,"cacheRead":0.00021329999999999998,"cacheWrite":0.0372435,"total":0.0382269}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775118350609,"responseId":"061d5b0f0f9c6a59a5c43fd0f297cafc"}}
